        <h3>The Life of a Bengal Tiger</h3>
        <p>The Bengal tiger, native to India and Bangladesh, is one of the most well-known tiger subspecies. They are known for their striking orange coat with black stripes.</p>
        
        <h3>Conservation Efforts</h3>
        <p>Due to poaching and habitat destruction, tigers are endangered. Conservation programs worldwide are working to protect these magnificent creatures.</p>
        
        <h3>Tiger Facts</h3>
        <p>Did you know that no two tigers have the same stripe pattern? Tigers also have powerful night vision, making them efficient nocturnal hunters.</p>
